						<p>You want to play soccer.</p>
						<p>You have the players, you have the ball, and you all know the rules.</p>
						<p>But you don't have a pitch.</p>
						<p>This is like trying to play multiplayer games without a server.</p>
						<p>If you want to play a game, you'll need a server.</p>
					<h2 class="mt-4 h3">What is a game server?</h2>
						<p><strong>A game server is a computer that acts as a central authority to define the current state of a multiplayer game. The server sends constant updates to players providing a snapshot of all elements in the game.</strong></p>
						<p>To break that down, the server is where the game is being played <em>and </em>the referee. When you jump, your computer tells that to the server, and the server tells everyone else that you’re in the air.</p>
					<h3 class="mt-4">Game servers keep everything in sync.</h3>
						<div class="col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-md-offset-1 my-4">
						<p class="noteBoxes imagebox">
							Image: Showing the flow of data from one individual to a server, and that server then bouncing that information out to all of the players in a web, showing data is also flowing from other players as well
