						<p>Both peer-to-peer and hosting from a home computer use one player’s home network.</p>
						<p>If they have poor internet, it’s a bad experience for everyone.</p>
						<p>In peer-to-peer, the networking will attempt the best connection, but the host's location can skew the ping to advantage certain players.</p>
						<p>Servers that are run from data centres have a lot of benefits over these two kinds of hosting.</p>
						<p>Most importantly: they are designed for and built with hosting multiplayer games in mind.</p>
						<p>The best experience for gamers is either dedicated servers from the developer or hosting their own dedicated server in a data centre.</p>
					<h2 class="mt-4 h3">Setting up a private dedicated gaming server</h2>
						<p>While many gamers enjoy playing on public servers, there are several advantages to setting up a private server.</p>
						<p>You'll need a specific game in mind when you start your server setup process. Whether it is a local or remote server, running your own dedicated game server will have benefits.</p>
						<p>Depending on the games played being the host of your own dedicated server, can also prevent players from interfering with your progress while you're offline!</p>
						<p>Whether choosing a server provider, using a separate PC to host locally, or running the dedicated server and game on the same computer, there is also increased control over the hardware in private dedicated servers.</p>
						<p>For example, if you need more memory for your dedicated server setup, that's possible with many providers. If it is your own hardware, you can simply upgrade it.</p>
						<p>Server software also means you can configure your game to have more control over who can join the game, moderation tools, and even mod support.</p>
					<h3 class="mt-4">What type of hardware is in a game server?</h3>
						<p>Physical game servers in data centres are large racks of computer components.</p>
						<p>Unlike servers for less intensive applications, game servers are designed to handle the high workloads of hosting multiplayer with immense amounts of CPU power and RAM.</p>
						<p>So players can join a server they have network switches to connect them to the internet and the players.</p>
